Subject: [duckbridge][be] Add DuckDbTypeHandler to the jdbc-scanner + DUCKDB factory case

What:
  Adds a first-class DuckDbTypeHandler to the BE be-java-extensions/jdbc-scanner
  and a `case "DUCKDB"` to JdbcTypeHandlerFactory.create(), so the duckbridge
  connector can emit `table_type = DUCKDB` and have JdbcJniScanner decode DuckDB
  result sets (read over quack-jdbc, jdbc:quack://...) with DuckDB-faithful
  ResultSet -> Doris coercions.

Why upstream needs it (and why it is BE-only):
  On the JdbcJniScanner path, `table_type` is just a free string selecting a
  value-coercion JdbcTypeHandler; JdbcTypeHandlerFactory's default returns
  DefaultTypeHandler (no TOdbcTableType enum gate, no throwing default -- that
  throwing gate is the LEGACY JdbcExecutorFactory path we do not use). No stock
  handler fits DuckDB cleanly:
    - DefaultTypeHandler : LARGEINT + VARBINARY, but NO ARRAY
    - ClickHouseTypeHandler: LARGEINT + ARRAY, but NO VARBINARY
    - TrinoTypeHandler   : ARRAY + VARBINARY, but DROPS LARGEINT (throws)
  DuckDB maps HUGEINT/UBIGINT -> LARGEINT, BLOB -> VARBINARY, LIST -> ARRAY, so
  it needs all three arms at once. One handler is strictly cleaner than
  contorting the FE type map to fit someone else's dialect.
  This change touches ONLY be-java-extensions/jdbc-scanner (Java): it needs NO
  thrift TOdbcTableType change and NO FE JdbcDbType change -- those bind only the
  legacy stock-catalog path duckbridge bypasses -- so it is a small,
  self-contained, reapplyable patch, and (per the plan) can rebuild just the
  jdbc-scanner jar to overlay into an existing BE image without a C++ rebuild.

Coverage (v1):
  - all scalars (bool, tinyint..bigint, float/double, DECIMAL<=38,
    date/datetime, char/varchar/string) -- same reads as DefaultTypeHandler.
  - LARGEINT  (DuckDB HUGEINT / UBIGINT) -> BigInteger, normalized defensively.
  - VARBINARY (DuckDB BLOB) -> byte[].
  - ARRAY     (DuckDB LIST) -> List, elements widened like ClickHouseTypeHandler
    (int128/wide-unsigned elements arrive as BigInteger).
  - STRUCT / MAP: NOT decoded in v1. The duckbridge FE maps DuckDB
    STRUCT/MAP/JSON to STRING/JSON, so they arrive as strings and take the
    scalar path. First-class nested decode is a follow-up (probe P4).

Upstream ask / exit criteria:
  Break this handler out into an upstream Doris PR before release, so a stock
  Doris carrying the fe-connector SPI can run duckbridge unpatched. When it
  lands in a release, this patch is deleted and BASELINE points at the tag.

Anchors at pin 5f009592035:
  NEW  fe/be-java-extensions/jdbc-scanner/.../org/apache/doris/jdbc/DuckDbTypeHandler.java
  EDIT fe/be-java-extensions/jdbc-scanner/.../org/apache/doris/jdbc/JdbcTypeHandlerFactory.java
       (inserts `case "DUCKDB": return new DuckDbTypeHandler();` after the
        existing `case "CLICKHOUSE"` arm)

Apply:  git apply --3way doris-patches/be/0001-duckdb-type-handler.patch
